The paper deals with information-theoretic limits of community detection in network models, which involves concepts from information theory, signal processing, and machine learning. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.IT (Information Theory). The paper also discusses the behavior of communities in real-world networks, which suggests that it may belong to cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) or cs.SD (Sound and Music Computing). The paper provides a geometrical representation of the relationships between different communities, which could fall under cs.LG (Machine Learning) or cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture).
